<subsection xml:id="subsec-area-of-regular-polygons" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Area of Regular Polygons</title>
     <introduction xml:id="auto_ob9e3r3z">
     <activity xml:id="auto_yujyceai">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_jcgvy619">
                <m>\textbf{Materials Needed:}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_ldxpueun">
                                    i.Compass,
                </p>
                            <p xml:id="auto_qr16ke35">
                    ii. Ruler
                </p>
                            <p xml:id="auto_b3ng0u3c">
                    ii. Protractor
                </p>
                            <p xml:id="auto_6p7nb5rw">
                    iv. Calculator
                </p>
                            <p xml:id="auto_j43ai0m3">
                    v. Pencil and paper
                </p>
                            <p xml:id="auto_bx5r3v2m">
                    vi. Colored pencils (optional)

                             <ul xml:id="auto_3jqpg7in">
                                <li xml:id="auto_hjm2ygft">
                                    <p xml:id="auto_duhjbg0r">
                                        Draw a line from the center O perpendicular to a side (e.g., side BC). This line is the apothem (denoted a). Label the apothem clearly.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                             </ul>
                            </p>

        </statement>
     </activity>
      <p xml:id="auto_vwfg08y7">
            <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m>
        </p>
     <p xml:id="auto_etfvpqqw">
        â™¦ The <m>\textbf{area}</m> of a <m>\textbf{regular polygon}</m> can be found using this formula, where <m>\textbf{P}</m>
        is the <m>\textbf{perimeter}</m> and <m>\textbf{a}</m>
        is the apothem
     </p>
      <p xml:id="auto_un1y64zj">
        The <m>\textbf{apothem}</m> is the distance from the center of a regular polygon to <m>\, \textbf{a} </m>side. Where <m> \textbf{a}</m> is the half <m>\frac{1}{2} \text{side.}</m>
     </p>
     <image width="50%">
     <latex-image label="polgon-triangle">
        \begin{tikzpicture}
            
            % Define hexagon vertices
            \def\R{3} % Radius of hexagon
            \foreach \i in {0,60,...,300} {
                \coordinate (P\i) at (\i:\R);
            }

            % Draw the hexagon
            \draw[thick] 
                (P0) -- (P60) -- (P120) -- (P180) -- (P240) -- (P300) -- cycle;

            % Define center
            \coordinate (C) at (0,0);
            
            % Draw the perpendicular segment
            \draw[dashed] (C) -- (0,-2.62) node[midway,left] {\Large $a$};

            % Right angle marker
            \draw[thick] (0,-2.35) -- (0.2,-2.35) -- (0.2,-2.62);
            % \draw (0,-\R)++(0,0) -- ++(0.2,0) -- ++(0,0.);

            % Mark the center point
            \draw[thick] (C) circle (2pt);
        \end{tikzpicture}
     </latex-image>
     </image>
    
     <p xml:id="auto_6hrlkpkt">
        You want to find the area of the triangle. You can see it has an apothem of
        <m>\sqrt{3}</m> meters and a side length of 10 meters.

     </p>
     <image width="50%">
        <latex-image label="polgon-hexagon">
            \begin{tikzpicture}
                            % Define triangle vertices
                \coordinate (A) at (-3,0);
                \coordinate (B) at (3,0);
                \coordinate (C) at (0,6); % Height of an equilateral triangle with side 6

                % Draw the equilateral triangle
                \draw[thick] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- cycle;
            
                % Label the side length
                \draw[thick] (A) -- node[left] {\Large 10 m} (C);
            
                % Define point E inside the triangle
                \coordinate (E) at (0,2.2);
                \coordinate (E1) at (1.5,3);
            
                % Draw perpendicular segment from E to side BC
                \draw[dashed] (E) -- (E1) node[above ,midway,rotate=40] {\large $\sqrt{3}$ m};
            
                %draw the right angle
                \tkzMarkRightAngle[draw=black,size=.2](B,E1,E);
            
                % Label the perpendicular length
            
                % Label point E
                \node[left] at (E) {\Large $A$};
                \draw[thick] (E) circle (2pt);
            \end{tikzpicture}
        </latex-image>
     </image>
        <p xml:id="auto_hu7x2dwi">
            If you also find the perimeter, P
,
        then you can use the formula A= <m> \frac{1}{2} \textbf{P}a</m> to find the area.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_x1wp53lx">
            <me>
                \textbf{P} = \text{length of each side } \times a \text{, where } a = h
            </me>
            
            <me>
                P = 10 \, \text{m} \times 3
            </me>
            <me>
                = 30, \text{m}
            </me>
            Now, use the formula for the area of a regular polygon is :
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_8jctyk83">
            <md>
                <mrow> A = \amp \frac{1}{2} \times 30 \times \sqrt{3} </mrow>
                <mrow> = \amp 125.98 \, \text{m}^2 </mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
        <example xml:id="auto_x2krxvru">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_dq9xi3c4">
                    A regular hexagon with center h is shown below
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_4lhdvgvh">
                 Similarly you can use <m>A = \frac{1}{2} \times n \times S \times a</m>
                </p>   
               
                <image width="60%">
     <latex-image label="polgon-hexagon-example">
        \begin{tikzpicture}
            

            % Define hexagon vertices
            \def\R{3} % Radius of hexagon
            \foreach \i in {0,60,...,300} {
                \coordinate (P\i) at (\i:\R);
            }

            % Draw the hexagon
            \draw[thick] 
                (P0) -- (P60) -- (P120) -- (P180) -- (P240) -- (P300) -- cycle;

            % Define center
            \coordinate (C) at (0,0) node[above] {\Large h};
            
            % Draw the perpendicular segment
            \draw[dashed] (C) -- (0,-2.62) node[midway,left] {\Large $14$ cm};

            % Right angle marker
            \draw[thick] (0,-2.35) -- (0.2,-2.35) -- (0.2,-2.62) node[below]{20 cm};
            % \draw (0,-\R)++(0,0) -- ++(0.2,0) -- ++(0,0.);

            % Mark the center point
            \draw[thick] (C) circle (2pt);
           
        \end{tikzpicture}
     </latex-image>
     </image>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                     <p xml:id="auto_55wx40em">Find the perimeter P, Then use the formula A= <m> \frac{1}{2} \textbf{P}a</m> to find the area.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_pgdse83y">
            <me>
                \textbf{P} = \text{length of each side } \times a
            </me>
            
            <me>
                P = 20 \, \text{cm} \times 6
            </me>
            <me>
                = 120 \, \text{cm}^2
            </me>
            Now, use the formula for the area of a regular polygon is :
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_x0r22ahs">
            <md>
                <mrow> A = \amp \frac{1}{2} \times 120 \times 14 \, \text{cm} </mrow>
                <mrow> = \amp 840 \text{cm}^2 </mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
         <p xml:id="auto_rcfjqgjg">
                    Where <m>n = \text{number of sides,} S = \text{length of each side and } a = \frac{S}{2}  </m>
                    
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_951lnqeu">
                    <md>
                        <mrow>A = \amp  \frac{1}{2} n \times S \times a</mrow>
                        <mrow> = \amp  \frac{1}{2} \times 6 \times 20 \, \text{cm} \times 14 \, \text{cm}</mrow>
                        <mrow> = \amp \frac{1,680}{2} \, \text{cm}^2</mrow>
                        <mrow> = \amp 840 \,\text{cm}^2 </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        
